IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO ENCOURAGE, PROMOTE, AND AID HUMAN- ITARIAN AND CHARITABLE RELIEF TO THE SICK AND SUFFERING BY SUPPORTING ST JOHN OF JERUSALEM EYE HOSPITAL GROUP & ST JOHN INTERNT'L IN LONDON.
IRS990.MissionDesc: THE ORGANIZATION WAS ESTABLISHED TO ENCOURAGE THE SPIRITUAL AND MORAL STRENGTHENING OF MANKIND IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE GREAT PRINCIPLE OF THE ORDER, PRO FIDE, AND TO PROMOTE THE RELIEF OF SICKNESS AND SUFFERING WITHOUT DISCRIMINATION OF RACE, GENDER, RELIGION, OR ABILITY TO PAY IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE SECOND GREAT PRINCIPLE OF THE ORDER, PRO UTILITATE HOMINUM. THE PRINCIPAL BENEFICIARIES OF THE PRIORY'S SUPPORT ARE AT ST JOHN JERUSALEM EYE HOSPITAL GROUP, THE WEST BANK, AND GAZA AND THE INTERNATIONAL ORDER OF ST JOHN IN LONDON.
IRS990.Desc: ST JOHN OF JERUSALEM EYE HOSPITAL GROUP, HEADQUARTERED IN EAST JERUSALEM WITH FACILITIES IN WEST BANK AND GAZA, TREATED 134,500 CHILDREN AND ADULTS IN 2021. IT IS THE ONLY CHARITY OPHTHALMIC HOSPITAL IN THE REGION. IT IS ALSO A TEACHING HOSPITAL TO TRAIN DOCTORS AND NURSES IN MUCH NEEDED OPHTHALMIC SPECIALTIES. THE PRIORY IN THE USA OF THE MOST VENERABLE ORDER OF THE HOSPIAL OF ST JOHN OF JERUSALEM (THE ORDER OF ST JOHN) MEMBERS HAVE VOWED TO PREVENT AND TREAT SICKNESS AND SUFFERING BY RAISING MILLIONS OF DOLLARS FOR THESE DESIGNATED CHARITIES. THEIR FUNDRAISING EFFORTS ARE ONGOING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: SCHEDULE D PART V PRIORY CHAPTER-DESIGNATED ENDOWMENT IS INVESTED FOR GROWTH AND INCOME IN RISK AVERSE VEHICLES TO SUPPLEMENT THE OPERATING NEEDS AND CHARITABLE GIVING OF THE PRIORY. THEY ARE GENERAL FUNDS WHICH MAY BE USED AS NECESSARY FOR UNANTICIPATED OPERATIONAL COSTS. BEFORE ACCESSING THE FUND, THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE OF THE PRIORY CHAPTER (THE GOVERNING BODY) MUST BE NOTIFIED AND BE PROVIDED SUFFICIENT RATIONALE TO JUSTIFY ITS USE. THE DREXEL FAMILY FUND IS A RESTRICTED ENDOWMENT FUND WHICH WILL SERVE IN PERPETUITY AND BE INVESTED IN RISK AVERSE VEHICLES WITH THE GOAL OF GENERATING INCOME. THE EARNINGS ON THE PRINCIPAL OF THE FUND WILL BE UTILIZED BY THE PRIORY IN THE USA IN LINE WITH THE RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE GOVERNING BODY OF THE PRIORY IN THE USA, BY DREXEL FAMILY MEMBERS OR THEIR REPRESENTATIVES. EARNINGS ON THE PRINCIPAL OF THE FUND SHALL BE UTILIZED, PROVIDED THAT SUCH RECOMMENDED UTILIZATION IS IN ACCORDANCE WITH THE MISSION OF THE PRIORY IN THE UNITED STATES.

ALL GRANTS TO FOREIGN ORGANIZATIONS ARE MONITORED AND REPORTED UPON VIA ANNUAL REPORTS, PROGRAM UPDATES, AND NEWSLETTERS AS WELL AS FACE TO FACE MEETINGS AND WRITTEN CORRESPONDENCE. TWO MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION SIT ON THE BOARD OF ST JOHN OF JERUSALEM EYE HOSPITAL GROUP AND ATTEND MEETINGS THREE TIMES PER YEAR AND REPORTS BACK TO OUR PRIORY CHAPTER ON A REGULAR BASIS. THE CHAIRMAN OF OUR PRIORY CHAPTER IS A MEMBER OF THE INTERNATIONAL GOVERNING BOARD OF THE MOST VENERABLE ORDER OF THE HOSPITAL OF ST JOHN OF JERUSALEM AND REPORTS BACK TO OUR MEMBERS AT THE ANNUAL MEETING AND TO OUR PRIORY CHAPTER AT QUARTERLY MEETINGS.
FROM 990 PART VI SECTION A LINE 6 THE MEMBERS ELECT THE PRIORY CHAPTER (GOVERNING BODY) ON AN ANNUAL BASIS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: MEMBERS OR STOCKHOLDERS THAT ELECT GOVERNING BODY MEMBERS
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 PART VI SECTION A LINE 7A MEMBERS VOTE AT THE ANNUAL MEETING TO APPROVE THE PRIORY CHAPTER WHO ARE NOMINATED BY THE PRIOR FOR A SET PERIOD OF TIME. ALL MEMBERS ARE GIVEN THE OPPORTUNITY TO VOTE EITHER IN PERSON OR BY PROXY. THE PROXY GIVES THE CHANCELLOR, THE TREASURER, AND THE SECRETARY THE AUTHORITY TO VOTE ON THE MEMBER'S BEHALF FOR THE ELECTION OF PRIORY CHAPTER MEMBERS AND ANY OTHER BUSINESS TRANSACTION WHICH MAY REQUIRE A VOTE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: GOVERNING BOARD DECISIONS APPROVED BY MEMBERS OR STOCKHOLDERS
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 PART VI SECTION A LINE 7B BY-LAW CHANGES AND RELATED MATTERS ARE SUBJECT TO APPROVAL BY MEMBERS OF THE ORGANIZATION WHO MAY VOTE EITHER IN PERSON AT THE MEETING OR BY PROXY.

FORM 990 PART VI SECTION B LINE 11B UPON PREPARATION BY AN INDEPENDENT CPA, MANAGEMENT REVIEWS THE 990 BEFORE FILING WITH THE IRS AND DISTRIBUTING TO THE GOVERNING BODY. SHOULD ANY SIGNIFICANT CLARIFICATIONS BE INDENTIFIED BY THE GOVERNING BODY, THEN AN AMENDED FORM WOULD BE FILED.

FORM 990 PART VI SECTION B LINE 12C ALL MEMBERS OF THE PRIORY CHAPTER ARE REQUIRED TO ANNUALLY SIGN A PERSONAL PLEDGE OF COMMITMENT AND DISCLOSE ANY POTENTIAL INTERESTS THAT COULD GIVE RISE TO CONFLICTS.

FORM 990 PART VI SECTION B LINES 15A AND 15B THE COMPENSATION OF ALL KEY EMPLOYEES IS REVIEWED UPON EMPLOYMENT AND ANNUALLY TO ENSURE IT IS A FAIR AND COMPETITIVE SALARY FOR SIMILAR POSITIONS AT SIMILAR SIZE ORGANIZATIONS. AN INDEPENDENT SOURCE IS USED TO PERFORM THIS REVIEW.

FORM 990 PART VI SECTION C LINE 19 THE GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY ARE AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST. THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE MADE AVAILABLE ON THE ORGANIZATION'S WEBSITE VIA THE ANNUAL REPORTS AND ALSO AVAILABLE UPON REQUEST.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: Form 990, Part IX, Line 19 - Conferences, Conventions & Meetings
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: Approximately every ten years, the U.S. Priory hosts the annual international meeting of the leadership of The Order of St John. The meeting includes the Officers of the Order and representatives of the Priories and associations from around the world. This governance meeting ensures consistency of goals and strategic plans across the organization, and provides an opportunity to leverage the talents and resources of the leadership.
